de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.semantics
Class Synset

java.lang.Object
  de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.abstracts.HasMonolingualExternalRefs
      de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.semantics.Synset
All Implemented Interfaces:
IHasDefinitions, IHasID, IHasMonolingualExternalRefs, java.lang.Comparable<Synset>
public class Synset
extends HasMonolingualExternalRefs
implements IHasID, IHasDefinitions, java.lang.Comparable<Synset>

Synset is a class representing the set of shared meanings within the same language. Synset links synonyms forming a synonym set. A Synset can link Sense instances of different LexicalEntry instances with the same part of speech.

Author:
Zijad Maksuti, Silvana Hartmann

getEquivalentsByLanguage

public java.util.List<Equivalent> getEquivalentsByLanguage(java.lang.String language)
Returns the List of all Equivalent instances of the Sense instances belonging to this Synset in a certain language. That is, the translations of all senses of the synset into a language specified by a language code, usually defined by a constant in ELanguageIdentifier.

Returns:
the list of all equivalents; might be empty, but never null.

getDefinitionText

public java.lang.String getDefinitionText()
Returns the definition text of this Synset instance. The returned text is extracted from first TextRepresentation instance of the first Definition of this synset.
If the first definition of this synset does not have a text representation, this method returns null.

Returns:
definition text of this synset or null if this synset does not have a definition text set
